{"evidence":["`cargo test --test unit minimal_flow_ -- --nocapture` passed (`flow_preset_test::minimal_flow_stage_order_matches_spec`, `flow_semantics_test::minimal_flow_semantics_match_spec`).","`cargo test --test unit built_in_flow_registry_exposes_all_five_presets_in_order -- --nocapture` passed.","`cargo test --test cli flow_list_prints_all_presets -- --nocapture` passed, but inspection shows that test still only asserts the legacy four preset names.","Static inspection found remaining hard-coded four-flow lists in `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs`, `src/contexts/automation_runtime/repo_registry.rs`, and `src/shared/error.rs`."],"findings_or_gaps":["High: `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs:295-303` and `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs:391-398` still validate `recommended_flow` against only `standard`, `quick_dev`, `docs_change`, and `ci_improvement`. Any requirements draft or synthesis payload that recommends `minimal` will now be rejected even though `minimal` is a built-in preset.","Medium: `src/contexts/automation_runtime/repo_registry.rs:19-30` omits `rb:flow:minimal` from `LABEL_VOCABULARY`. GitHub/daemon label bootstrap will not provision the new routing label, so label-based routing to the `minimal` flow is incomplete.","Low: `src/shared/error.rs:23-25` still says the supported presets are only `standard, quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement`. Unknown-flow errors now present incorrect user guidance after adding `minimal`."],"follow_up_or_amendments":["Update the requirements-drafting contract validation to derive built-in presets from `FlowPreset::all()` (or equivalent shared source) and add unit coverage that `recommended_flow = minimal` is accepted for both draft and synthesis payloads.","Add `rb:flow:minimal` to the daemon label vocabulary and update the related conformance coverage in `src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs:14331-14349` so future presets cannot drift from GitHub label provisioning.","Fix the `InvalidFlowPreset` message in `src/shared/error.rs` and strengthen CLI/discovery tests so they explicitly assert `minimal` appears in supported-flow output."],"outcome":"request_changes"}